<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 12:43AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>A wintry mix of light snow, sleet, freezing rain and rain will
transition to all rain through 1am as temperatures rise into the
mid to upper 30s. Untreated roads may remain snow covered and
locally icy through around 3am as road temperatures lags air
temperatures in rising above freezing. Thereafter, road surfaces
should warm safely above freezing and be just wet.</description>
